1
00:01:34,820 --> 00:01:36,450
Mr. Wahlberg.

2
00:01:37,950 --> 00:01:40,700
Why did you call for all of us?

3
00:01:41,240 --> 00:01:46,620
Hiding the fact he's a Lackmagic and attending
Easton Academy is out of the question.

4
00:01:47,120 --> 00:01:48,960
There's no need for an inquiry.

5
00:01:49,380 --> 00:01:53,090
We need to abide by the rules
and give this boy the maximum penalty.

6
00:01:53,710 --> 00:01:59,840
Divine Visionaries, might I ask you
to defer his sentencing?

7
00:02:00,090 --> 00:02:04,970
This is the first time
Innocent Zero sent a messenger.

8
00:02:05,220 --> 00:02:10,480
There is a high chance this boy
will give us a lead on them.

9
00:02:12,310 --> 00:02:15,730
We can't afford
to lose him at this juncture.

10
00:02:21,160 --> 00:02:25,330
Huh? The headmaster
seems really important.

11
00:02:25,450 --> 00:02:26,750
You know...

12
00:02:26,750 --> 00:02:29,370
Mr. Wahlberg is a previous Divine Visionary.

13
00:02:30,120 --> 00:02:35,170
He's a living legend, the only one to go
toe-to-toe against Innocent Zero in his youth.

14
00:02:35,590 --> 00:02:40,590
And the only one that I,
the next top dog of the world, respect.

15
00:02:40,590 --> 00:02:43,680
He's a man among magic users.

16
00:02:44,140 --> 00:02:45,680
Listen closely.

17
00:02:46,100 --> 00:02:47,140
'Kay.

18
00:02:48,640 --> 00:02:52,690
Mr. Wahlberg, I understand your position.

19
00:02:53,860 --> 00:02:56,230
But I cannot accept it.

20
00:02:57,230 --> 00:02:59,650
Regulations exist to maintain order.

21
00:03:00,110 --> 00:03:02,990
Lackmagic should be purged.

22
00:03:03,530 --> 00:03:05,450
That's just the way...

23
00:03:10,540 --> 00:03:12,540
Mr. Wahlberg, please!

24
00:03:13,380 --> 00:03:16,880
It's true. He cannot use magic.

25
00:03:16,880 --> 00:03:22,180
He's a bit rough around the edges
and not too scholarly.

26
00:03:22,640 --> 00:03:29,100
However, he has an unusual gift
to sway people's hearts.

27
00:03:29,850 --> 00:03:36,150
I believe that people like him will change
how we perceive this world.

28
00:03:36,900 --> 00:03:39,570
Of course, that is not all.

29
00:03:39,860 --> 00:03:44,570
Until now, those without magic
have been treated as inferior.

30
00:03:45,320 --> 00:03:50,700
But I take some issue
with that unjust treatment.

31
00:03:51,120 --> 00:03:55,670
Our values change alongside history.

32
00:03:56,090 --> 00:04:00,920
However, redefining our values
takes courage

33
00:04:01,220 --> 00:04:05,640
as we must admit
our injustices thus far.

34
00:04:06,350 --> 00:04:08,260
That said...

35
00:04:08,760 --> 00:04:13,270
What is wrong is still wrong.

36
00:04:14,310 --> 00:04:16,110
Mr. Wahlberg.

37
00:04:16,190 --> 00:04:22,070
I respect your position, but ignoring rules
and forcing your opinion...

38
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:25,240
I ask of you as well.

39
00:04:25,780 --> 00:04:27,450
Rayne, even you?

40
00:04:28,530 --> 00:04:31,580
I do agree with the headmaster's opinion,

41
00:04:32,080 --> 00:04:36,580
but Mash Burnedead has also
proven himself worthy of our trust.

42
00:04:37,380 --> 00:04:39,170
Including my trust.

43
00:04:42,510 --> 00:04:45,430
<i>So you like rabbits?</i>

44
00:04:45,630 --> 00:04:47,930
<i>No, not that.</i>

45
00:04:48,260 --> 00:04:51,310
Rayne, I know what you're getting at.

46
00:04:51,310 --> 00:04:53,930
But sentimental opinions
shouldn't change regulations.

47
00:04:53,930 --> 00:04:57,810
What a pain. Follow the book
and get this over with.

48
00:04:58,110 --> 00:05:01,530
Mr. Wahlberg, you are quite right to say so.

49
00:05:01,530 --> 00:05:04,280
But the public won't allow
such an exception.

50
00:05:05,360 --> 00:05:10,580
There's nothing to reconsider.
Lackmagics need to be purged.

51
00:05:11,120 --> 00:05:15,580
You're letting emotions
take priority over rational thought.

52
00:05:16,250 --> 00:05:20,380
My thoughts align with yours.

53
00:05:21,170 --> 00:05:26,800
Our magical power
is a special gift from God.

54
00:05:26,970 --> 00:05:32,100
It's natural for those without it
to be excluded.

55
00:05:32,520 --> 00:05:36,520
That's because they aren't the same as us.

56
00:05:36,520 --> 00:05:42,570
However, one Lackmagic
just saved my life.

57
00:05:42,820 --> 00:05:45,990
I know that
I should be following regulations.

58
00:05:46,860 --> 00:05:50,950
If I am being remiss in my duties, so be it.

59
00:05:50,950 --> 00:05:55,620
But this case was mine to process.

60
00:05:56,040 --> 00:06:01,670
I would like you to defer
his sentencing if possible.

61
00:06:02,040 --> 00:06:05,420
You may punish me as you see fit.

62
00:06:05,420 --> 00:06:09,130
But I will not change my verdict.

63
00:06:17,640 --> 00:06:19,560
Only under these conditions.

64
00:06:20,060 --> 00:06:27,070
He will act only under our supervision
as a pawn against Innocent Zero.

65
00:06:27,530 --> 00:06:32,700
And he must prove he's strong enough
to fight Innocent Zero.

66
00:06:33,870 --> 00:06:37,960
That proof is to become this year's
Divine Visionary candidate.

67
00:06:40,920 --> 00:06:44,040
Should you fail,
you will be purged immediately.

68
00:06:44,210 --> 00:06:45,960
After all, it's only a deferment.

69
00:06:47,170 --> 00:06:49,720
All right. Understood.

70
00:06:50,430 --> 00:06:55,470
But to embody the headmaster's wishes
and for me to live in peace with everyone...

71
00:06:56,520 --> 00:06:58,480
That alone won't be enough.

72
00:07:12,490 --> 00:07:16,040
I will beat Innocent Gyro up.

73
00:07:16,910 --> 00:07:18,290
With my fist.

74
00:07:30,670 --> 00:07:32,890
And that's what happened.

75
00:07:33,050 --> 00:07:35,050
Innocent Zero.

76
00:07:35,510 --> 00:07:39,060
You have to go against
such a dangerous organization?

77
00:07:39,060 --> 00:07:41,850
So you can't use magic?

78
00:07:41,850 --> 00:07:42,690
Nope.

79
00:07:43,480 --> 00:07:46,270
<i>Trying to win against me without magic?</i>

80
00:07:46,520 --> 00:07:48,900
You really couldn't use magic.

81
00:07:48,900 --> 00:07:49,780
Nope.

82
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:52,910
Gotcha. Then let's go out and have fun.

83
00:07:53,780 --> 00:07:55,280
<i>Wait, what now?</i>

84
00:07:58,450 --> 00:08:00,830
A sudden suggestion to go have fun.

85
00:08:00,830 --> 00:08:04,420
Maybe Dot was worried about Mash.

86
00:08:04,710 --> 00:08:09,090
They did defer the sentencing,
so this is probably better than sulking.

87
00:08:09,300 --> 00:08:12,840
But I wonder what kind of street clothes
everyone will wear.

88
00:08:13,010 --> 00:08:14,220
Here I am!

89
00:08:14,640 --> 00:08:17,300
KAKLANG

90
00:08:15,760 --> 00:08:17,300
Full-plate armor!?

91
00:08:17,930 --> 00:08:20,810
I mean, fun is basically a battle.

92
00:08:21,020 --> 00:08:22,560
<i>What the heck does that mean?</i>

93
00:08:22,560 --> 00:08:24,100
I'm here now.

94
00:08:24,230 --> 00:08:26,020
That must be Mash.

95
00:08:25,310 --> 00:08:26,730
RLL RLL

96
00:08:26,980 --> 00:08:28,690
He's in full workout mode!

97
00:08:29,400 --> 00:08:33,650
I've never gone out with friends before,
so I wasn't sure what to wear.

98
00:08:33,650 --> 00:08:36,570
But did you really need that ab wheel?

99
00:08:36,870 --> 00:08:38,200
<i>My goodness.</i>

100
00:08:38,330 --> 00:08:41,830
<i>I really don't want to be seen
with these two.</i>

101
00:08:41,830 --> 00:08:43,250
Sorry I'm late.

102
00:08:46,750 --> 00:08:48,960
<i>I'm glad Lance is in normal...</i>

103
00:08:49,590 --> 00:08:51,210
LITTLE SISTER LOVE

104
00:08:49,920 --> 00:08:51,210
- Love.
- Cringe!

105
00:08:52,340 --> 00:08:54,470
Did she just wink? And talk!?

106
00:08:54,680 --> 00:08:58,140
Yeah, come at me from anywhere!

107
00:08:58,720 --> 00:09:01,270
Dear sister, you're cute today, too.

108
00:09:02,430 --> 00:09:05,230
<i>This group is just so detestable!</i>

109
00:09:08,440 --> 00:09:13,110
There's a famous game you can play
only here in Marchétte Street.

110
00:09:13,530 --> 00:09:14,240
See, over there.

111
00:09:16,240 --> 00:09:18,320
TICKLE TICKLE

112
00:09:23,660 --> 00:09:30,790
A tickle koala's snot hardens, so we play darts
by tickling its nose and making it sneeze.

113
00:09:31,300 --> 00:09:33,550
Oh! Sounds like fun.

114
00:09:33,550 --> 00:09:34,800
I'll try it.

115
00:09:39,220 --> 00:09:40,180
TICKLE TICKLE

116
00:09:40,390 --> 00:09:43,930
Well, it's hard for novices
to even hit the target.

117
00:09:43,930 --> 00:09:44,810
THUNK

118
00:09:46,520 --> 00:09:48,190
Sorry, Dot.

119
00:09:48,600 --> 00:09:51,820
Well, it's your first time.

120
00:09:52,530 --> 00:09:54,570
I'll show you how it's done.

121
00:09:55,820 --> 00:09:58,070
TICKLE TICKLE

122
00:10:01,700 --> 00:10:02,830
THUNK

123
00:10:06,080 --> 00:10:07,790
A flying arm bar?

124
00:10:07,960 --> 00:10:11,630
- All right! Fight's on, damn it!
- Let's go.

125
00:10:12,500 --> 00:10:14,300
- Let's go.
- Okay.

126
00:10:16,550 --> 00:10:18,220
A new wand?

127
00:10:18,220 --> 00:10:21,930
Yeah. I've been wanting
to try out a new wand.

128
00:10:22,350 --> 00:10:27,560
And lately, there are rumors that
the Divine Visionary Candidate Exam is near.

129
00:10:30,060 --> 00:10:35,070
Because of the Innocent Zero case,
the exam will be held earlier this year.

130
00:10:35,230 --> 00:10:38,320
But that works in our favor.

131
00:10:39,570 --> 00:10:43,870
Based on the coin count,
we're sure to be taking the selection exam.

132
00:10:44,410 --> 00:10:48,540
If we can pass that, the only thing left
is the final screening.

133
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:51,540
Even though you can't use magic...

134
00:10:51,880 --> 00:10:55,170
For my sister's sake,
I'm not going to go easy on you.

135
00:10:57,550 --> 00:10:58,670
We're here.

136
00:10:59,430 --> 00:11:00,470
This is the place.

137
00:11:19,110 --> 00:11:20,700
Welcome.

138
00:11:21,740 --> 00:11:23,780
Easton kids, are ye?

139
00:11:23,780 --> 00:11:25,080
Oh, yes.

140
00:11:26,660 --> 00:11:28,040
So many different kinds.

141
00:11:28,040 --> 00:11:31,210
The wand shop is always nothing but hype!

142
00:11:31,460 --> 00:11:33,830
Maybe I should replace my wand, too.

143
00:11:48,270 --> 00:11:49,850
Wowee.

144
00:11:49,850 --> 00:11:52,600
Your magical power
summons a fitting wand.

145
00:11:52,600 --> 00:11:55,690
Wands are tools for releasing magical power.

146
00:11:56,190 --> 00:12:00,240
Basically extensions
of the magic users' bodies.

147
00:12:00,400 --> 00:12:05,700
A fitting wand can drastically improve
your magic too.

148
00:12:06,160 --> 00:12:09,330
I think my magical power went up
because of my classes thanks to my wand.

149
00:12:09,540 --> 00:12:13,080
That's why you need to periodically
gauge your magic and...

150
00:12:18,590 --> 00:12:23,550
It's better to choose a wand
that fits your current self.

151
00:12:29,970 --> 00:12:31,430
Impressive.

152
00:12:31,430 --> 00:12:36,650
Even among wands for double-liners,
that one is quite the item.

153
00:12:37,770 --> 00:12:38,730
Amazing.

154
00:12:38,730 --> 00:12:39,900
I don't like it!

155
00:12:41,030 --> 00:12:43,490
You're not gauging?

156
00:12:43,490 --> 00:12:44,150
Huh?

157
00:12:44,360 --> 00:12:48,620
<i>Oh, no! Mash lacks magical power,
so no wand would react to him.</i>

158
00:12:48,620 --> 00:12:49,990
Then, I guess...

159
00:12:50,160 --> 00:12:51,160
<i>You're doing it?</i>

160
00:13:03,090 --> 00:13:06,300
What's that wand? The one on the floor.

161
00:13:07,600 --> 00:13:11,060
RTTL RTTL RTTL

162
00:13:09,100 --> 00:13:11,060
Huh? Scary. What the...

163
00:13:11,350 --> 00:13:16,690
Oh, that? We've had that wand here
in this shop for ages.

164
00:13:16,770 --> 00:13:21,190
It's so heavy that nobody can ever lift it.

165
00:13:21,860 --> 00:13:27,280
It's said that elf water
springs up from beneath it,

166
00:13:27,450 --> 00:13:33,250
and magnificent wands
can be crafted using that water.

167
00:13:34,410 --> 00:13:38,000
But it's no more than a legend.

168
00:13:38,420 --> 00:13:46,380
No amount of muscle or magic has been able
to lift it for the past millennium.

169
00:13:46,380 --> 00:13:48,840
That's bad, old man!
Saying that to him would...

170
00:13:48,840 --> 00:13:50,470
You don't get it at all!

171
00:13:51,760 --> 00:13:53,470
What do you mean?

172
00:13:56,440 --> 00:13:58,650
H-Hey, what are you...

173
00:14:04,570 --> 00:14:06,110
Then, I'll take this one.

174
00:14:12,790 --> 00:14:14,620
Thank you so much.

175
00:14:14,790 --> 00:14:16,910
That wand is all yours.

176
00:14:16,910 --> 00:14:17,870
Yay.

177
00:14:18,120 --> 00:14:19,420
Freaky.

178
00:14:19,670 --> 00:14:23,210
<i>In the end, Lance didn't buy a wand.</i>

179
00:14:23,590 --> 00:14:26,840
I'm sorry, my chores
took longer than expected!

180
00:14:26,840 --> 00:14:29,130
I had some bamboo-siness to do!

181
00:14:29,470 --> 00:14:31,680
Lemon. Captain.

182
00:14:32,600 --> 00:14:34,810
All right! We're gonna play!

183
00:14:50,280 --> 00:14:53,330
We're living our best student lives!

184
00:14:55,080 --> 00:14:56,200
That was fun.

185
00:14:57,790 --> 00:15:01,330
I've never gone out with friends before.

186
00:15:02,710 --> 00:15:04,500
Let's come back again sometime.

187
00:15:05,250 --> 00:15:07,130
- Yup.
- Damn straight!

188
00:15:07,130 --> 00:15:08,340
Let's come again!

189
00:15:08,340 --> 00:15:09,970
Next time with my sister, too.

190
00:15:09,970 --> 00:15:11,590
Buh-Buh-Bamboo!

191
00:15:15,310 --> 00:15:17,850
<i>And several days passed.</i>

192
00:15:18,600 --> 00:15:22,350
Gold coin count, one, two, three...

193
00:15:23,190 --> 00:15:24,480
Seven.

194
00:15:25,400 --> 00:15:29,820
Preparation for the selection exam
is as good as done.

195
00:15:30,070 --> 00:15:31,530
It's finally time.

196
00:15:33,280 --> 00:15:34,490
But first...

197
00:15:35,530 --> 00:15:37,660
You're going to visit home?

198
00:15:38,410 --> 00:15:42,000
Now? Right before the selection exam?

199
00:15:42,630 --> 00:15:44,380
Are you serious?

200
00:15:44,840 --> 00:15:48,630
I'm sorry. I-I-I will stay.

201
00:15:50,420 --> 00:15:53,010
Well, I think I'll go back home.

202
00:15:53,340 --> 00:15:56,010
<i>Wait, what was that flashback just now?</i>

203
00:15:58,520 --> 00:16:01,850
Someone lacking magic
wants to be a Divine Visionary.

204
00:16:01,850 --> 00:16:03,440
This is unprecedented.

205
00:16:03,900 --> 00:16:06,860
Headmaster Wahlberg is getting on in years.

206
00:16:07,270 --> 00:16:09,990
He can no longer make rational decisions.

207
00:16:10,860 --> 00:16:16,700
Those in power have a responsibility
to stop disturbances before they arise.

208
00:16:17,240 --> 00:16:20,000
So, I have to do something about this.

209
00:16:21,160 --> 00:16:23,370
Let me be clear.

210
00:16:24,080 --> 00:16:29,420
See that he cannot participate
in the Divine Visionary Candidate Exam.

211
00:16:30,300 --> 00:16:34,720
Orca dorm prefect, Margarette Macaron.

212
00:16:35,430 --> 00:16:41,060
Ortie, it's unusual
that you'd ask me for a favor.

213
00:16:41,310 --> 00:16:47,270
But you know I don't march
to the beat of just anyone's drum.

214
00:16:48,610 --> 00:16:52,570
I only care about one thing.

215
00:16:54,950 --> 00:16:56,570
Stimulation.

216
00:16:57,620 --> 00:17:00,330
There should be no lack of that.

217
00:17:00,660 --> 00:17:05,580
Mash Burnedead
bested Lang's prefect, Abel.

218
00:17:05,790 --> 00:17:11,340
Abel the coin seeker, you say?
Hmph, that's not bad.

219
00:17:11,670 --> 00:17:14,880
But simply hoarding coins
doesn't measure stren—

220
00:17:14,880 --> 00:17:16,970
He did it without magic.

221
00:17:19,720 --> 00:17:22,680
Leave the cleanup to me.

222
00:17:23,770 --> 00:17:25,350
Go wild.

223
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:35,840
Spring has arrived.

224
00:18:36,670 --> 00:18:38,930
<i>So creepy.</i>

225
00:18:39,800 --> 00:18:42,470
Oh, Mash!

226
00:18:42,470 --> 00:18:45,180
I'm glad you made it back here, Mash!

227
00:18:45,180 --> 00:18:46,930
I'm somehow surviving.

228
00:18:48,810 --> 00:18:50,860
You hanging in there?

229
00:18:50,860 --> 00:18:54,440
Y-Yes. E-Easy peasy.

230
00:18:54,440 --> 00:18:56,400
R-Really?

231
00:18:57,110 --> 00:18:58,650
Excuse us!

232
00:18:59,030 --> 00:19:00,530
Huh? No way.

233
00:19:01,070 --> 00:19:02,950
You can't be...

234
00:19:03,160 --> 00:19:07,710
What? Mash's friends?

235
00:19:08,290 --> 00:19:11,960
I'm so touched.
To think Mash has made friends...

236
00:19:12,750 --> 00:19:17,210
Because I wasn't able to expose him
to the outside world,

237
00:19:17,460 --> 00:19:19,970
I didn't think this day would come.

238
00:19:19,970 --> 00:19:22,930
We're not such superficial things like friends.

239
00:19:22,930 --> 00:19:23,720
Huh?

240
00:19:24,050 --> 00:19:26,220
You use the word "rival"
and read it as "buddy."

241
00:19:26,470 --> 00:19:28,430
Though, I'm tougher than him.

242
00:19:28,680 --> 00:19:30,060
<i>He's even got a rival.</i>

243
00:19:30,230 --> 00:19:32,270
Father-in-law, it's nice to meet you.

244
00:19:32,270 --> 00:19:37,570
I give my regards for the future.
I am Mash's future wife.

245
00:19:37,780 --> 00:19:39,820
Even a fiancée!?

246
00:19:39,950 --> 00:19:42,870
We haven't even held hands,
so rest assured.

247
00:19:44,280 --> 00:19:48,700
Please be at ease.
Mash is doing well at school.

248
00:19:49,910 --> 00:19:52,500
This isn't much,
but please have some herbal tea.

249
00:19:52,500 --> 00:19:53,710
Oh, thank you.

250
00:19:53,710 --> 00:19:56,170
That's so not like you.

251
00:19:56,460 --> 00:19:58,090
I have something for you, too.

252
00:19:59,130 --> 00:20:00,840
- Please have some merch.
- Of who?

253
00:20:00,970 --> 00:20:01,840
My little sister.

254
00:20:01,840 --> 00:20:03,010
Why!?

255
00:20:03,640 --> 00:20:07,640
He doesn't understand that everyone
has different priorities.

256
00:20:07,640 --> 00:20:09,350
I-I see.

257
00:20:14,060 --> 00:20:19,610
They're quite unique. All of them.

258
00:20:19,610 --> 00:20:21,280
Yes, they are.

259
00:20:21,860 --> 00:20:23,820
You must have a hard time.

260
00:20:23,820 --> 00:20:24,990
Yes.

261
00:20:25,780 --> 00:20:26,620
But...

262
00:20:28,540 --> 00:20:33,250
I was never able to let Mash
go outside until now.

263
00:20:33,960 --> 00:20:38,000
I never dreamed he'd be surrounded
by such wonderful friends.

264
00:20:40,630 --> 00:20:43,800
I hope it lasts forever.

265
00:20:45,430 --> 00:20:46,760
I'm sure...

266
00:20:47,220 --> 00:20:49,560
I'm sure it will.

267
00:20:53,020 --> 00:20:55,690
Hope they won't mind us barging in.

268
00:20:56,020 --> 00:20:59,150
To defeat Abel
so soundly without magic.

269
00:20:59,150 --> 00:21:01,990
You think I can let
someone like that slide?

270
00:21:02,650 --> 00:21:06,160
Hey, what was that boy's name?

271
00:21:06,370 --> 00:21:07,530
Mash.

272
00:21:07,530 --> 00:21:09,200
It's Mash Burnedead.

273
00:21:09,200 --> 00:21:12,200
Right, right. Mash Burnedea—

274
00:21:26,800 --> 00:21:28,050
Dear me.

275
00:21:28,390 --> 00:21:31,020
You're playing his bodyguard now?

276
00:21:31,020 --> 00:21:33,350
I just happened to pass by.

277
00:21:34,140 --> 00:21:38,270
I heard a nasty-sounding laughter over here.

278
00:21:39,230 --> 00:21:42,570
Well, well. If it isn't the Sword Cane...

279
00:21:42,780 --> 00:21:46,570
Divine Visionary, Rayne Ames.

280
00:21:47,360 --> 00:21:54,500
<i>Orca prefect Margarette Macaron's evil hands
approach by Orter Madl's order.</i>

281
00:21:54,960 --> 00:21:57,330
<i>But Mash is still oblivious of it. </i>

282
00:21:57,500 --> 00:21:59,840
All right, let's play a board game!

283
00:21:59,840 --> 00:22:01,420
Yeah!

284
00:22:01,420 --> 00:22:03,550
<i>He really didn't know.</i>

285
00:23:35,220 --> 00:23:39,940
NEXT EPISODE
RAYNE AMES AND GOD'S GIFT

